<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 07 at 3:01AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Beaver
and northeastern Texas Counties through 330 AM CDT...
At 301 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southeast of Feterita, moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Hooker, Tyrone and Baker.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
